THE HONEYPOT ROUTE LAYER (api/src/honeypot.ts)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Fake routes that no legitimate user ever touches. Triggering any of them
fires a CRITICAL-severity HONEYPOT_TRIGGERED audit event:

  /admin, /admin/*              → fake admin panel (common scanner target)
  /api/login                   → fake login (real path is /api/auth/email/login)
  /api/admin/login              → fake admin login
  /phpMyAdmin, /phpmyadmin      → both casing variants registered
  /wp-admin                    → WordPress scan detection
  /wp-login.php                → WordPress scan detection
  /.env                        → environment file grab attempt
  /config.php                  → config file scan

  Plus: SQL injection probe detection on all paths. Scans for 'union',
  'select', 'drop table', 'delete from', '--', '/*', '*/', 'xp_' in URL
  and body. Skipped on /api/auth/ and file upload paths where user input
  is legitimate.

An attacker that recons the surface before targeting specific endpoints
lights up the honeypot before they reach anything real.


