THE BLOCKCHAIN ANCHOR — TAMPER-EVIDENT DAILY RECORD
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Every day's block count is written to the operationsAuditLog as event type
FCGBDS_DAILY_BLOCKCHAIN_EVENT and anchored to a SHA-256 hash chain. Each
anchor includes the previous day's hash (previousAnchor) so the chain can
be traversed and any alteration to historical block counts would invalidate
all subsequent anchors.

The 14 anchor hashes shown in the production data section above are the
actual values returned by the live API. They are publicly checkable.


