━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The bot problem does not have a proprietary solution. The reason bots win is
not because detection is technically impossible — it is because every platform
that solves it does so in isolation, behind a wall, and the bot operators
simply route around that wall by targeting the unprotected neighbor.

I have proven that one person — one solo indie dev powered by AI — can build
a system that detects 100% of known adversarial bot categories across 6 attack
types and 326,320 test runs, with no third-party black-box service, no
expensive ML infrastructure, and no secret sauce that requires a PhD to
understand. I have 3,324 permanently anchored real-traffic blocks on the
ledger. I have the code. I have the live numbers.

I am releasing it because:

1. Bots are an industry-wide problem. They do not respect your platform
   boundaries. Your bot wave is my bot wave. Sharing the defense layer is
   the only rational response.

2. The collective signal corpus is worth more than any single platform's
   data. When the bridge receives a signal from one partner that a particular
   source class at a particular confidence level correlates with bot behavior,
   every platform on the bridge benefits from that signal immediately.

3. I need adoption to make Proof-of-Rot work. My token economy only functions
   if the engagement it rewards is real. The more platforms that run this
   system and report into the shared bridge, the more confident we can be that
   the engagements we reward are legitimate. This is not altruism — it is
   infrastructure I need to exist, and open sourcing it is how we get it built
   at the scale it needs to be.

4. The IRL noise never stops. Governance bodies debate. Platform terms teams
   write policy. Standards organizations meet quarterly. Bots operate in
   milliseconds. The only people who can build something fast enough to matter
   are the ones who care enough to actually build it and share it.

I built it. I'm sharing it.

The bots don't care which platform you are.
The rest of us shouldn't either.

This is the light. Come build it with us.


